---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy — Deal Lens">
  <h1>Deal Lens Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="muted">Last updated: April 11, 2026</p>

  <p>
    Deal Lens is a Chrome extension published by Walensis that analyzes resale
    listings on Facebook Marketplace, eBay, and Reverb to estimate fair market
    value and identify good deals. This policy explains what data Deal Lens
    collects, how it's used, and your rights. For the company-level policy,
    see the <a href="/privacy">Walensis privacy policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Data we collect</h2>

  <h3>From listing pages you view</h3>
  <p>
    When you click to analyze a listing, the extension extracts the following
    from the page you're viewing:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Listing title, price, and condition</li>
    <li>Listing description (when present)</li>
    <li>Up to 5 listing photos</li>
    <li>Listing URL and platform (Facebook Marketplace, eBay, or Reverb)</li>
    <li>Item category (when present)</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Deal Lens does <strong>not</strong> extract or collect:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Your browsing history</li>
    <li>Pages or listings you don't explicitly analyze</li>
    <li>Personal data from the listing page (seller names, profiles, messages)</li>
    <li>Anything outside the listing you're actively viewing</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>From your account</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Your email address (via Google sign-in)</li>
    <li>A unique API key we generate for your account</li>
    <li>Usage counts (number of analyses per day) for rate limiting</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How we use your data</h2>
  <p>
    When you analyze a listing, the listing data is sent to our API and used to:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Identify the product using AI analysis of the title, description, and photos</li>
    <li>Search eBay and Reverb for comparable listings</li>
    <li>Calculate an estimated fair market value</li>
    <li>Return the analysis to your browser</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Listing data is processed <strong>in memory only</strong> and is not stored
    in a database. We do not log, retain, or share the contents of listings you
    analyze.
  </p>
  <p>
    Your email and API key are stored to authenticate requests, enforce usage
    limits, and let you sign back in.
  </p>

  <h2>Third parties we share data with</h2>
  <p>To provide the analysis, listing data is sent to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Anthropic</strong> (Claude AI) — listing title, description,
      photos, and search results are sent to Claude for product identification
      and analysis. Anthropic does not train its models on data sent through
      their API. See
      <a href="https://www.anthropic.com/legal/privacy">Anthropic's privacy policy</a>.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>eBay</strong> — listing titles are used to query eBay's Browse
      API for comparable listings.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Reverb</strong> — listing titles are used to query Reverb's
      GraphQL API for comparable music gear listings.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p>For account management, we use:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Supabase</strong> — handles authentication (Google sign-in) and
      stores your account record. See
      <a href="https://supabase.com/privacy">Supabase's privacy policy</a>.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Google Sign-In</strong> — used only to verify your email address.
      We do not request access to your Google account, contacts, calendar, or
      any other Google data.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    We do <strong>not</strong> sell data, share data with advertisers, or use
    any analytics or tracking services.
  </p>

  <h2>Data retention</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Listing data:</strong> not retained. Processed in memory and discarded.</li>
    <li><strong>Account data:</strong> retained until you delete your account.</li>
    <li><strong>Usage counts:</strong> retained for 30 days for rate limiting purposes.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>You can:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Delete your account</strong> by signing in and clicking "Delete account" in settings, or by emailing us</li>
    <li><strong>Request a copy</strong> of any data associated with your account</li>
    <li><strong>Stop using Deal Lens</strong> at any time by uninstalling the extension</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    To exercise any of these rights, email
    <a href="mailto:privacy@walensis.com">privacy@walensis.com</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>
    Deal Lens is not intended for users under 13, and we do not knowingly
    collect data from children.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    If we make material changes to this policy, we will update the "Last
    updated" date and notify users via the extension on next launch.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this policy? Email
    <a href="mailto:privacy@walensis.com">privacy@walensis.com</a>.
  </p>
</Layout>
